cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel approach based on convolutional neural networks for the detection and segmentation of microcalcification clusters in mammography imaging. It could also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with the detection of early signs of breast cancer. Additionally, it involves the use of deep learning techniques, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves the analysis of medical images to aid radiologists in their examination.
